This paper deals with game theory and decision making under uncertainty, which are core topics in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on repeated games with cumulative prospect theoretic preferences, which is a subfield of game theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design). The paper also discusses learning and convergence of empirical distributions, which are topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence and Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also uses concepts from probability theory and statistics, which are relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper discusses equilibria and convergence, which are topics in economics, making cs.EC (Economics and Computation) a possible category as well.
